aspguidp.controller.input

Class InputActionController

  • java.lang.Object
    • aspguidp.controller.input.InputActionController

  • public class InputActionController
extends java.lang.Object
    Controller class of the input action area of the application. The input action area contains buttons which are used to trigger various actions on or with the data of the input area of the program.

    Currently, the input action area contains a save button, a load button and a run button. The save button saves the current input data of the input area to a problem instance file. The load button sets the data of the input area of the program by a problem instance file. The run button executes the logic program with the data of the input area of the application.

    This class is the link between the data of the input components (InputElementController)(which is accessed over the input atom hub) and the logic program solver, as it queries the input data from the input atom hub and passes them to the logic program solver.
